    "created_at": "2014-06-23T18:30:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-06-23T18:30:25Z",
    "body": "As a language change, this has no RFC corresponding with it, but it's small enough that it may be ok to discuss here instead.\n\nI personally would like to keep indexing. It is a fact that all our strings are utf-8 encoded, and that fact will never change. The type system will very quickly tell you you're getting a byte and not a char.\n",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
