    "created_at": "2014-06-23T19:09:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-06-23T19:09:03Z",
    "body": "It seems that we have a bit of a push-back from any byte-based methods on strings, but there are so many that I think it's ergonomically infeasible to remove all of them. It seems a little odd to remove half but leave the other half, leading to my opinion that this is a nice sugar that should stick around.\n",
